-- Australia Defeats England by 267 Runs to Tie Ashes Cricket Series at 1-1
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2010-12-19T03:24:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-19/australia-defeats-england-by-267-runs-to-tie-ashes-cricket-series-at-1-1.html
Australia beat England by 267 runs
in the third Ashes cricket Test in Perth to tie the series at
1-1 with two matches to play.  Ryan Harris took 6-47 as the home team bowled England out
for 123 before lunch on day four at the WACA Ground after
setting it 391 for victory. Recalled fast bowler Mitchell
Johnson finished with nine wickets in the match.  The fourth Test in Melbourne starts Dec. 26 before the
series concludes from Jan. 3 in Sydney.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  